Right now topics default to sort by popularity. You can force a topic to the top of the list by making it a featured topic. As we continue to add more topics, it would be nice for users to be given the option to sort alphabetically, so they can find topics they may want to watch easier.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-51774].
  {panel}

Currently you can search a KB (a Confluence space) from the Service Desk home screen before you create a request, it would be great to have CQ questions show up in the results there as well.

I had a chat to Gil, who said they can modify their existing UI to also search on a set of labels, but they'd need us to modify the Confluence capabilities API to include information about whether or not CQ is installed.

Once we've added that they can modify their search.

