Confluence Questions makes sense as an add-on for Confluence but it would also be great to be able to purchase, license and deploy it separately from Confluence.

{panel:title=Atlassian Status as of May 6, 2014|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3C78B5| titleBGColor=#3C78B5| bgColor=#E7F4FA}
Hi All,

You cannot currently license Confluence Questions separately from Confluence. However, as of [Confluence 5.5|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Confluence+5.5+Release+Notes] there is a "Confluence Spaces" plugin that you can disable which would "turn off" the spaces functionality and only have Confluence Questions appear for users.  

Bill Arconati,
Group Product Manager
{panel}

