As a CQ administrator of a software company, I need to create and uphold guidelines for asking questions in order to get people the answers they are looking for. One of those guidelines is the ability to restrict who can create new topics to ensure that all questions are within logical topics as defined by our application components.

There might be a "implement more thorough permissions" case out there but I was not able to find one

Thanks!

