One is required to grant full administrator access to Confluence in order to allow users/groups to be Confluence Questions administrators.

In order to allow specific users/groups to edit/delete existing questions, I would like to grant administrative privileges to Confluence Questions *only*, not Confluence as a whole.

This can be done by adding an extra column to /admin/questions/viewpermissions.action next to "use confluence questions" that says "administer confluence questions".

