{panel:title=Atlassian Status as of Sept 23rd, 2015|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#205081| titleColor=#FFFFFF| titleBGColor=#205081 | bgColor=#E7F4FA}
Hi Everyone,
Thank you for your patience with this feature request. The public REST API for Confluence Questions is now available in version 2.3.0 and above. You can find out what you can do with it on this *[documentation page|https://docs.atlassian.com/confluence-questions/rest/index.html]*.

We would appreciate one minute of our time filling out a very short survey to help us understand what you hope to do with a REST API. To do so please fill out the following survey:
h4. → [Provide feedback with Confluence Questions REST API Survey|https://atlassian.wufoo.com/forms/confluence-questions-rest-api/]
Cheers,
The Confluence Questions team
{panel}




