If the Questions for Confluence add-on is installed with restricted permissions, all users still see the "Ask a question" button in the sidebar while performing a search. This leads them to a "Not Permitted" page. To prevent this, we had to disable the Search Sidebar 'Ask A Question' module. Unfortunately, this hides the button for all Confluence users.

The Search Sidebar 'Ask A Question' module should respect the global permissions of Questions for Confluence.
